title: SFH to visit Guangzhou and Shenzhen
content_text:
p>
    The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, will begin a two-day 
    visit to Guangzhou and Shenzhen tomorrow (October 29) to strengthen ties and 
    hold meetings with the relevant Mainland authorities on various issues 
    including medical and health care, Chinese medicine, food supply and food 
    safety. On his arrival in Guangzhou, Dr Ko will call on the Director-General of the 
    Health Department of Guangdong Province, Professor Yao Zhibin, to exchange

Health Department of Guangdong Province, Professor Yao Zhibin, to exchange 
    views on health and medical issues between the two sides. In the afternoon, 
    Dr Ko will visit the Guangdong Provincial Hospital of Traditional Chinese 
    Medicine to learn about its operation. He will also meet the Director of the 
    Guangdong Entry-Exit Inspection and Quarantine Bureau, Ms Li Yanhui, to 
    forge closer co-operation and exchange between the two places on food safety

forge closer co-operation and exchange between the two places on food safety 
    as well as inspection and quarantine. Dr Ko will leave for Shenzhen on the morning of October 30 to call on the 
    Director General of the Shenzhen Entry-Exit Inspection and Quarantine 
    Bureau, Mr Liu Shengli, and visit the Bureau's testing laboratory to learn 
    about the latest facilities for inspection and quarantine of food supplied 
    to Hong Kong. Before returning to Hong Kong in the afternoon, Dr Ko will

to Hong Kong. Before returning to Hong Kong in the afternoon, Dr Ko will 
    tour the University of Hong Kong-Shenzhen Hospital. Joining Dr Ko on the visit will be the Permanent Secretary for Food and 
    Health (Food), Mrs Marion Lai, and the Director of Health, Dr Constance 
    Chan.
